biography.bio: Gustav Knuth was born on 7 July 1901 in Brunswick, Germany. After he received acting lessons from Casimir Paris, a well known actor at that time, he made his stage debut at the Stadttheater Heidelberg in 1918. Later, he played in Hamburg and also in Basel, Switzerland, but finally returned to Hamburg. In 1935, his first movie Der Ammenkönig (1935) became a unexpected success and many more such as the legendary Port of Freedom (1944) or the Sissi (1955) trilogy in the 1950s followed. After World War II, his stage career continued in Switzerland, where he lived in Küsnacht and was ensemble member at the Schauspielhaus Zurich. On 1 February 1987, he died of a stroke in Neu-Münster near Zurich, Switzerland.
biography.name: Gustav Knuth

biography.bio: Ruth-Maria Kubitschek was born on August 2, 1931 in Komotau, Czechoslovakia. She is an actress, known for Frau Ella (2013), Das Erbe der Guldenburgs (1987) and Freunde fürs Leben (1992). She was previously married to Götz Friedrich.
biography.name: Ruth-Maria Kubitschek

biography.bio: Evelyn Gressmann was born on December 1, 1943 in Berlin, Germany. She is an actress, known for Drei Damen vom Grill (1977), Das Ferienschiff (1968) and Großer Ring mit Außenschleife (1966).
biography.name: Evelyn Gressmann

biography.bio: Kurt Pratsch-Kaufmann was born on September 1, 1906 in Dresden, Germany. He was an actor, known for Johannes and the 13 Beauty Queens (1951), Thérèse Raquin (1966) and Großer Ring mit Außenschleife (1966). He was married to Marianne Pohlenz. He died on June 24, 1988 in Munich, Bavaria, West Germany.
biography.name: Kurt Pratsch-Kaufmann

biography.bio: Walter Feuchtenberg was born on February 7, 1923 in Nuremberg, Germany. He is an actor, known for Papiermühle (1962), Sest uprchlíku (1970) and Betriebsfest (1966).
biography.name: Walter Feuchtenberg

biography.bio: Horst Janson was born on October 4, 1935 in Mainz-Kastel, Wiesbaden, Hesse, Germany. He is an actor, known for Captain Kronos - Vampire Hunter (1974), Murphy's War (1971) and The Last Days of Patton (1986). He has been married to Helgardt 'Hella' Ruthardt since July 10, 1982. They have two children. He was previously married to Monika Lundi.
biography.name: Horst Janson

biography.bio: Herbert Tiede was born on March 3, 1915 in Osnabrück, Germany as Herbert Salomon. He was an actor, known for Fais ta valise Sherlock Holmes (1960), Wo blieb Friedrich Weisgerber? (1966) and Gestatten - Mein Name ist Cox (1961). He died on January 12, 1987 in Munich, Bavaria, West Germany.
biography.name: Herbert Tiede

biography.placeOfBirth: Free City of Danzig [now Gdansk, Pomorskie, Poland]
biography.bio: Jürgen Janza was born on December 4, 1934 in Free City of Danzig. He is an actor, known for Doppelter Einsatz (1994), Ein ehrenwerter Herr (1968) and Valentin Katajews chirurgische Eingriffe in das Seelenleben des Dr. Igor Igorowitsch (1967).
biography.name: Jürgen Janza

biography.bio: Lutz Hochstraate was born on January 7, 1942 in Dortmund, Germany. He is an actor and assistant director, known for Woobinda, Animal Doctor (1968), Pfarrer in Kreuzberg (1977) and Der Schuft, der den Münchhausen schrieb (1979).
biography.name: Lutz Hochstraate

biography.bio: Karl Hellmer was born on March 11, 1896 in Vienna, Austria-Hungary. He is known for his work on The Bridge (1949), Schwarz auf Weiß (1963) and The Captain from Köpenick (1956). He was married to Selma Dietl. He died on May 18, 1974 in West Berlin, West Germany.
biography.name: Karl Hellmer

biography.bio: Herbert Knippenberg was an actor, known for The Law (1959), Die Heirat (1965) and Das Ende vom Lied (1963). He died on September 25, 1970 in Bremen, Germany.
biography.name: Herbert Knippenberg

biography.bio: Kurt Ebbinghaus is an actor, known for Ein Bild fürs Leben (1954), Das salomonische Frühstück (1956) and Die eiskalte Nacht (1960).
biography.name: Kurt Ebbinghaus

biography.bio: Peter Martin Urtel was born on August 25, 1914 in Berlin, Germany. He was an actor, known for Circle of Deceit (1981), Fünftausend Mark Belohnung (1942) and Wie starb Dag Hammerskjöld? (1975). He died on January 16, 1989 in Sommerhausen, Bavaria, Germany.
biography.name: Peter Martin Urtel

biography.bio: Horst-Werner Loos was born in 1915. He was an actor, known for Krieg im dritten Stock (1973), Ein später Gast (1962) and Zwischen den Zügen (1961). He died in 1981.
biography.name: Horst-Werner Loos

biography.bio: Ursula Grabley was born on December 8, 1908 in Woltersdorf, Brandenburg, Germany as Ursula Margarete Marie Feodora Grabley. She was an actress, known for Chasse à l'homme (1938), Kampf um Blond (1933) and Annette in Paradise (1934). She was married to Viktor de Kowa. She died on April 3, 1977 in Brilon, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany.
biography.name: Ursula Grabley
